he%20newly%20arrived%20Crew-10%20crew.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20previous%20launch%20date%20for%20Crew-10%20was%20no%20earlier%20than%20late%20March.%20The%20Crew-10%20mission%20will%20carry%20NASA%20astronauts%20Anne%20McClain%2C%20and%20Nichole%20Ayers%2C%20Japan%20Aerospace%20Exploration%20Agency%20astronaut%20Takuya%20Onishi%2C%20and%20Roscosmos%20cosmonaut%20Kirill%20Peskov%2C%20to%20the%20space%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20earlier%20launch%20opportunity%20is%20available%20following%20a%20decision%20by%20mission%20management%20to%20adjust%20the%20agency's%20original%20plan%20to%20fly%20a%20new%20Dragon%20spacecraft%20for%20the%20Crew-10%20mission%20which%20requires%20additional%20processing%20time%2C%20according%20to%20NASA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20flight%20now%20will%20use%20a%20previously%20flown%20Dragon%2C%20called%20Endurance%2C%20and%20joint%20teams%20are%20working%20to%20complete%20assessments%20of%20the%20spacecraft's%20previously%20flown%20hardware%20to%20ensure%20it%20meets%20the%20agency's%20Commercial%20Crew%20Programme%20safety%20and%20certification%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20comes%20as%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20asked%20SpaceX%20CEO%20Elon%20Musk%20to%20facilitate%20the%20return%20of%20both%20Williams%20and%20Wilmore%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMusk%20claimed%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bterrible%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20pair%20were%20left%20%26quot%3Bstranded%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20ISS%20for%20so%20long%2C%20even%20though%20NASA%20had%20already%20roped%20in%20SpaceX%20months%20ago%20to%20return%20both%20astronauts%20as%20part%20of%20its%20Crew-9%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWilliams%20and%20Wilmore%20have%20been%20stuck%20in%20space%20since%20June%20last%20year%20due%20to%20technical%20problems%20with%20Boeing's%20Starliner%20which%20took%20them%20to%20ISS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20