%20with%20a%20male%20heir%20continues.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnDisappointing%2C%20but%20not%20surprising%20-%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnPS%20-%20I%20have%20a%20girl%20and%20I%20have%20heard%20from%20100s%20of%20people%20to%20give%20birth%20to%20a%20boy%20next.%20It%20feels%20horrible%20when%20people%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F1jP81E0QT3%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F1jP81E0QT3%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Naveena%20(%40TheNaveena)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FTheNaveena%2Fstatus%2F1889517482395967635%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EFebruary%2012%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EChiranjeevi%20has%20been%20married%20to%20Surekha%20since%201980.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739339880000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fhuplfmco_chiranjeevi-_625x300_12_February_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fchiranjeevi-in-soup-over-sexist-remark-scared-ram-charan-might-have-a-daughter-again-asked-him-for-a-son-7691536%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chiranjeevi%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20I'm%20a%20ladies'%20hostel%20warden%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fchiranjeevi-in-soup-over-sexist-remark-scared-ram-charan-might-have-a-daughter-again-asked-him-for-a-son-7691536%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22List%20Of%20World's%20Most%20Corrupt%20Country%20Is%20Out.%20What's%20India's%20Rank%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDenmark%20is%20the%20least%20corrupt%20country%20in%20the%20world%20followed%20by%20Finland%2C%20Singapore%20and%20New%20Zealand%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Corruption%20Perceptions%20Index%20(CPI)%20for%202024%2C%20which%20serves%20as%20a%20barometer%20of%20public%20sector%20misconduct%20worldwide.%20The%20report%20compiled%20by%20Transparency%20International%20placed%20India%20at%2096th%20spot%2C%20three%20positions%20drown%20from%20the%20previous%20year's%20rank.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transparency.org%2Fen%2Fcpi%2F2024%2Findex%2Find%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindex%3C%2Fa%3E%20ranks%20180%20countries%20and%20territories%20by%20their%20perceived%20levels%20of%20public%20sector%20corruption%20according%20to%20experts%20and%20business%20people%2C%20using%20a%20scale%20of%20zero%20to%20100%2C%20where%20%26quot%3Bzero%26quot%3B%20is%20highly%20corrupt%20and%20%26quot%3B100%26quot%3B%20is%20very%20clean.%20The%202024%20report%20highlighted%20that%20corruption%20is%20a%20dangerous%20problem%20in%20every%20part%20of%20the%20world%2C%20but%20a%20change%20for%20the%20better%20is%20happening%20in%20many%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20list%2C%20in%202024%2C%20India's%20overall%20score%20was%2038%20while%20it%20was%2039%20in%202023%20and%2040%20in%202022.%20India's%20rank%20in%202023%20was%2093.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20India's%20neighbours%2C%20Pakistan%20at%20135th%20position%2C%20and%20Sri%20Lanka%20at%20121st%20spot%20grappled%20with%20their%20respective%20low%20rankings.%20Bangladesh's%20ranking%20stood%20further%20down%20at%20149%2C%20while%20China%20ranked%2076.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20countries%20had%20their%20worst%20showing%20in%20more%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20including%20leading%20powers%20such%20as%20the%20United%20States%20and%20France%20to%20authoritarian%20nations%20such%20as%20Russia%20and%20Venezuela.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20dropped%20from%2069%20points%20to%2065%20and%20landed%20in%20the%2028th%20position%20from%2024th%20place%20earlier.%20Other%20Western%20nations%20on%20the%20decline%20included%20France%2C%20which%20slid%20four%20points%20to%2067%20and%20five%20places%20to%2025th%3B%20and%20Germany%2C%20which%20dropped%20three%20points%20to%2075%20and%20six%20places%20to%2015th.%20It%20tied%20with%20Canada%2C%20which%20was%20down%20one%20point%20and%20three%20places.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMexico%20also%20dropped%20five%20points%20to%2026%20as%20the%20judiciary%20failed%20to%20take%20action%20in%20major%20corruption%20cases%2C%20Transparency%20International%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20which%20already%20declined%20significantly%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20shed%20another%20four%20points%20to%2022%20last%20year.%20Transparency%20International%20noted%20that%20Moscow's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022%20has%20%26quot%3Bfurther%20entrenched%20authoritarianism.%26quot%3B%20It%20said%20that%20Ukraine%2C%20while%20its%20score%20dipped%20one%20point%20to%2035%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20making%20strides%20in%20judicial%20independence%20and%20high-level%20corruption%20prosecutions.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20Sudan%20slid%20to%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20index%20with%20just%20eight%20points%2C%20displacing%20Somalia%20although%20the%20latter%20country's%20score%20dropped%20to%20nine.%20They%20were%20followed%20by%20Venezuela%20with%2010%20and%20Syria%20with%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETransparency%20International%20noted%20that%20%26quot%3Bglobal%20corruption%20levels%20remain%20alarmingly%20high%2C%20with%20efforts%20to%20reduce%20them%20faltering%26quot%3B%20in%202024.%20While%2032%20countries%20have%20significantly%20reduced%20their%20corruption%20levels%20since%202012%2C%20there%20is%20still%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20work%20to%20be%20done%20as%20148%20countries%20have%20stayed%20stagnant%20or%20gotten%20worse%20during%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ECorruption's%20Effect%20On%20Climate%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20also%20pointed%20to%20worldwide%20risks%20from%20corruption%20to%20efforts%20to%20combat%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20Follow%2C%20No%20Index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transparency.org%2Fen%2Fpress%2F2024-corruption-perceptions-index-corruption-playing-devastating-role-climate-crisis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclimate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20said%20that%20a%20lack%20of%20transparency%20and%20accountability%20mechanisms%20increases%20the%20risk%20of%20climate%20funds%20being%20embezzled%20or%20misused%2C%20while%20%26quot%3Bundue%20influence%2C%26quot%3B%20often%20from%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20obstructs%20the%20approval%20of%20ambitious%20policies%2C%20hindering%20progress%20in%20reducing%20emissions%20and%20adapting%20to%20the%20unavoidable%20effects%20of%20global%20heating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHuge%20numbers%20of%20people%20around%20the%20world%20suffer%20severe%20consequences%20of%20global%20heating%2C%20as%20funds%20intended%20to%20help%20countries%20cut%20greenhouse%20gas%20emissions%20and%20protect%20vulnerable%20populations%20are%20stolen%20or%20misused.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20corruption%20in%20the%20form%20of%20undue%20influence%20obstructs%20policies%20aimed%20at%20addressing%20the%20climate%20crisis%20and%20leads%20to%20environmental%20damage%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProtecting%20climate%20mitigation%20and%20adaptation%20efforts%20from%20corruption%20will%20make%20these%20life-saving%20activities%20more%20effective%20and%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20benefit%20people%20in%20need%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20countries%20with%20high%20CPI%20scores%20have%20the%20resources%20and%20power%20to%20drive%20corruption-resistant%20climate%20action%20around%20the%20world%20but%20instead%2C%20they%20often%20serve%20the%20interests%20of%20fossil-fuel%20companies%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20these%20countries%20are%20also%20home%20to%20financial%20hubs%20that%20attract%20illicit%20funds%20stemming%20from%20corruption%2C%20environmental%20destruction%20and%20other%20crime.%20While%20the%20CPI%20does%20not%20measure%20this%2C%20dirty%20money%20poses%20a%20major%20corruption%20problem%20with%20harmful%20effects%20that%20reach%20far%20beyond%20these%20countries'%20borders%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECorruption%20is%20an%20evolving%20global%20threat%20that%20does%20far%20more%20than%20undermine%20development%20--%20it%20is%20a%20key%20cause%20of%20declining%20democracy%2C%20instability%20and%20human%20rights%20violations.%20The%20international%20community%20and%20every%20country%20must%20make%20tackling%20corruption%20a%20top%20and%20long-term%20priority%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20crucial%20to%20pushing%20back%20against%20authoritarianism%20and%20securing%20a%20peaceful%2C%20free%20and%20sustainable%20world.%20The%20dangerous%20trends%20revealed%20in%20this%20year's%20Corruption%20Perceptions%20Index%20highlight%20the%20need%20to%20follow%20through%20with%20concrete%20action%20now%20to%20address%20global%20corruption%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739339820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fajmv5vto_corruption-afp_625x300_12_February_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fcorruption-perceptions-index-2024-south-sudan-is-worlds-most-corrupt-country-denmark-least-indias-rank-is-7691265%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Denmark%20is%20the%20least%20corrupt%20country%20in%20the%20world%20followed%20by%20Finland%2C%20Singapore%20and%20New%20Zealand%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Corruption%20Perceptions%20Index%20(CPI)%20for%202024%2C%20which%20serves%20as%20a%20barometer%20of%20public%20sector%20misconduct%20worldwide.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fcorruption-perceptions-index-2024-south-sudan-is-worlds-most-corrupt-country-denmark-least-indias-rank-is-7691265%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20Harshvardhan%20spoke%20about%20dating%20Kim%20Sharma%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A173