C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fopenai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ecomplicated%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20organization.%20As%20is%20often%20the%20case%2C%20Matt%20Levine%20at%20Bloomberg%20has%20a%20very%20useful%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fopinion%2Farticles%2F2025-02-11%2Fsure-elon-musk-might-buy-openai%3Fsrnd%3Dundefined%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexplainer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20it%20boils%20down%20to%20this%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERight%20now%2C%20OpenAI%20is%20a%20nonprofit%20organization%20that%20controls%20a%20very%20valuable%20business.%20It's%20the%20group%20that%20created%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20other%20AI%20properties%2C%20and%20it%20has%20even%20grander%20plans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20leader%20Sam%20Altman%20wants%20to%20convert%20OpenAI%20into%20a%20for-profit%20business%2C%20and%20plans%20on%20giving%20the%20nonprofit%20part%20of%20OpenAI%20a%20stake%20in%20the%20for-profit%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMusk%20and%20his%20theoretical%20co-investors%20argue%20that%20this%20is%20a%20sweetheart%20deal%20that%20will%20short-change%20OpenAI%2C%20the%20nonprofit%20company.%20So%20they're%20offering%20to%20buy%20the%20nonprofit%20part%20of%20OpenAI%20for%20%26quot%3Bno%20less%20than%20%2497.375%20billion%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20a%20letter%20from%20Marc%20Toberoff%2C%20an%20attorney%20representing%20the%20Musk%20coalition.%20(I've%20asked%20both%20Toberoff%20and%20OpenAI%20for%20comment.)%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20have%20to%20summarize%20something%20with%20three%20bullet%20points%2C%20it's%20already%20pretty%20complicated.%20But%20it%20gets%20more%20complicated%20from%20here%2C%20because%20now%20we%20have%20to%20guess%20at%20whether%20Musk%20actually%20plans%20on%20doing%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20conventiona